data.description: Welcome to your charming 1960s two-story home nestled near Lake Overholser! This timeless residence seamlessly blends that vintage layout with the large spacious bedrooms upstairs, but with some modern touches that give a more updated feel downstairs. There is plenty of counter space in the kitchen for food prepping, and stainless steel appliances. The living room has a gas fireplace to keep you warm and cozy during the winter months and built-in shelving to show off your most prized possessions. The dining room and living room open up to each other, while the dining room and kitchen open up to each other.  There is a downstairs bathroom that gives guests an opportunity to use without having to go upstairs. Retreat upstairs and you will find the primary bedroom upstairs has room for a desk, large dressers, an on-suite bathroom, along with two closets and access to some attic storage. New vinyl flooring downstairs and carpet upstairs. The on-suite bathroom provides a buffer between the primary bedroom and the middle bedroom. The third bedroom has two closets and an extra space that includes a built-in desk area. There is an enclosed porch off the living room that leads to the shaded backyard, which comes in handy during our hot summer months. The backyard has a view of a large lot behind the house, which exudes a more private setting. The close proximity to the lake and all the activities it offers can enhance one's quality of life if they enjoy the outdoors. There is biking and jogging trails, fishing, kayaking near by.
